        <presentation>&lt;p&gt;Two cars of equal inertia, m, are driving at the same speed, v.  Both are going at constant speed.  Car 1 is going over the crest of a hill and car 2 is going through the bottom of a valley.  Both pieces of road can be thought of as pieces of circles of radius, R.  The road certainly exerts a vertical force on both.  What can we say about the magnitudes of these vertical forces?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/cars_hill_dip.png" alt="Two cars, one at top of hill, one at bottom of dip" width="500" height="261" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</presentation>
